title: Here's The Washington Post sports cover: Oct. 15, 2015
text:
By Dan Worthington October 15 at 12:11 AM Follow @danworthington At 2 p.m. on Wednesday, the original cover lineup was (and I’m using sports department lingo) Caps, Steinberg, Redskins, Jays and Wiz. 
The story on Washington Redskins wide receiver DeSean Jackson was our planned display — but that was before a bat got hit and another got flipped in Toronto. 
Our cover switch was a go. With a large advertisement on the bottom of the front (not pictured), one story had to move inside. This gave us a little more room to keep the Jackson story prominent and create the real estate necessary for the baseball display. 
The fun started with head suggestions for the ALDS Game 5 between the Blue Jays and Rangers. 7th-inning flip
